fields.title: Recovery Day
fields.description: Recovery day to allow training adaptations to occur. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Basic Endurance
fields.description: Steady endurance ride in zone 1. Stay within the target intensity range the majority of the time. Keep your cadence up.

fields.title: Long Basic Endurance
fields.description: Steady endurance ride in zone 1. Stay within the target intensity range the majority of the time. Keep your cadence up. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour and keep hydrated.

fields.title: Steady Endurance
fields.description: Endurance ride in Zone 2. Stay within the target intensity range the majority of the time. Keep your cadence up.

fields.title: Long Basic Endurance
fields.description: Endurance ride in Zone 2. Stay within the target intensity range the majority of the time. Keep your cadence up. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour and keep hydrated.

fields.title: Endurance Ramp
fields.description: A ramp through Zone 2 and into Zone 3 to increase aerobic threshold. Maintain the target intensity and cadence for each step.

fields.title: Endurance with Sprints
fields.description: Endurance ride in Zone 2 with sprints. Focus on high cadence rather than power for the sprints. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour and keep hydrated.

fields.title: Long Endurance
fields.description: Endurance ride in Zone 2. Stay within the target intensity range the majority of the time. Keep your cadence up. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour and keep hydrated.

fields.title: Strength Endurance Ramps
fields.description: Low cadence during the strength endurance intervals is key. Increased strength endurance will help improve climbing ability. If at any point your knees complain, revert to normal cadence.

fields.title: Strength Endurance Ramps
fields.description: Low cadence during the strength endurance intervals is key. Increased strength endurance will help improve climbing ability. If at any point your knees complain, revert to normal cadence.

fields.title: Endurance with Zone 3 Climbs
fields.description: Aim to complete the low cadence zone 3 intervals on a climb. If at any point your knees complain, revert to normal cadence. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Threshold Blocks
fields.description: Threshold blocks at 'sweetspot' and then at FTP aiming to raise anaerobic threshold. Lift the cadence for the FTP efforts.

fields.title: Under Over Threshold
fields.description: Threshold blocks under and over FTP. Make sure to raise your cadence for the 30 second pushes above anaerobic threshold. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Endurance with Zone 4 Intervals
fields.description: Endurance ride with Zone 4 intervals. Zone 4 intervals can be completed on a hill or on the flat. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: VO2max Intervals
fields.description: Zone 5 VO2max intervals. Note the primer minute before each interval to elevate heart rate. Maintain a high cadence for the VO2max intervals. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: VO2max Microbursts
fields.description: Zone 5 VO2max mircoburst intervals. 40 seconds 'ON' in Zone 5 at a high cadence followed by 20 seconds 'OFF' in Zone 2. Note the 1 minute primer before each interval to raise your heart rate. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Endurance with Zone 5 Intervals
fields.description: Endurance ride with Zone 5 intervals. Zone 5 intervals ideally to be completed uphill, but could be on the flat. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: VO2max Microbursts
fields.description: Short, but high intensity Zone 5 & 6 intervals to maintain or improve VO2max. Microburst intervals as either 20 second 'ON', high cadence in Zone 6, 20seconds 'OFF' in Zone 2 or 40 seconds 'ON' in Zone 5 and 20 seconds 'OFF' in Zone 2. Note the 1 minute primer before each interval to raise your heart rate. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: VO2max Microbursts, Extended
fields.description: Short, but high intensity Zone 5 & 6 intervals to maintain or improve VO2max. Microburst intervals as either 20 second 'ON', high cadence in Zone 6, 20seconds 'OFF' in Zone 2 or 40 seconds 'ON' in Zone 5 and 20 seconds 'OFF' in Zone 2. Note the 1 minute primer before each interval to raise your heart rate. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Anaerobic Intervals
fields.description: After a thorough warm up there are a mixture of 1 minute and 30 second anaerobic efforts. These are best performed on a false flat or uphill if possible.

fields.title: Anaerobic Intervals, Extended
fields.description: After a thorough warm up there are a mixture of 1 minute and 30 second anaerobic efforts. These are best performed on a false flat or uphill if possible.

fields.title: Endurance with Zone 6 Intervals
fields.description: Endurance ride with Zone 6 intervals. Zone 6 intervals ideally to be completed uphill, but could be on the flat. Fuel with 40-60g of carbohydrate per hour. Keep hydrated.

fields.title: Sprint Intervals
fields.description: After a thorough warm up there is a set of high cadence 'jumps', where the focus is on accelerating quickly in a smaller gear. There are two all out sprints to finish. This session is best performed outdoors on a quiet road.

fields.title: Mixed Sprint Intervals
fields.description: After a thorough warm up there is a set of high cadence 'jumps', where the focus is on accelerating quickly in a smaller gear. The low cadence wind ups should be done in a hard gear from a slow speed. There are two all out sprints to finish. This session is best performed outdoors on a quiet road.

fields.title: Endurance with Zone 7 Sprints
fields.description: Endurance ride with a set of high cadence 'jumps', where the focus is on accelerating quickly in a smaller gear. Finish with a set of all out sprints. This session is best performed outdoors on quiet roads for the sprint segments.
